
A version control system also goes by SCM (Source Control Management tool) or VCS (Version Control System).

{ Some History Bites


  Early 1970s - M. J. Rochkind: SCCS (Source Code Control System). Possibly the first VCS on Unix.

  Early 1980s - Walter F. Tichy: RCS (Revision Control System)

  1986 - Dick Grune: CVS (Concurrent Version System)

  2001: SVN (Subversion)

}
